  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear the lamb shoulder until browned on all sides, then set aside.",
    "Add more oil if necessary, then sauté the onion, garlic, and ginger until softened.",
    "Add the cumin, cinnamon, paprika, cayenne pepper (if using), salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the chicken broth and bring to a simmer.",
    "Return the lamb to the pot, cover, and transfer to the oven.",
    "Braise the lamb for 2 1/2 hours, or until tender and falling apart.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven and let it cool slightly.",
    "Shred the lamb with two forks and stir in the pecorino-romano cheese.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional pecorino-romano cheese if desired."
  ],
